.TH COATL 1 "February 2026" "Coatl" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
coatl \- build Coatl sources to native Linux binaries
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B coatl
.I build input.coatl
[\fB--emit=\fRasm|ir|obj|bin|cbyte]
[\fB-o\fR \fIoutput\fR]
[\fB--arch=\fRx86_64|aarch64]
.br
.B coatl
.I run-cbyte input.cbyte
.br
.B coatl
[\fB--help\fR|\fB-h\fR]
.br
.B coatl
[\fB--version\fR|\fB-V\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBcoatl\fR is the command-line launcher for the Coatl compiler pipeline.
It compiles Coatl sources to various native and intermediate formats.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B build
Compile a \fI.coatl\fR source file. The default emission is a native binary.
.TP
.B run-cbyte
Execute a Coatl bytecode file using the built-in VM.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--emit=\fRasm|ir|obj|bin|cbyte
Choose emitted output kind (default: \fBbin\fR).
.TP
\fB-o\fR \fIoutput\fR
Write output to the given path.
.TP
\fB--arch=\fRx86_64|aarch64
Select target architecture. Default is auto-detected.
.TP
\fB--help\fR, \fB-h\fR
Show usage help.
.TP
\fB--version\fR, \fB-V\fR
Show version string.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBCOATL_ARCH\fR
Default architecture when \fB--arch\fR is omitted.
.TP
\fBCOATL_VERSION\fR
Fallback version string if Git metadata is unavailable.
.TP
\fBCOATL_HOME\fR
Path to Coatl runtime assets (contains \fItools/\fR).
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success and non-zero on error.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
\fBcoatl build examples/hello.coatl -o /tmp/hello\fR
Compile to native binary.
.TP
\fBcoatl build examples/hello.coatl --emit=asm -o /tmp/hello.s\fR
Compile to x86_64 assembly.
.TP
\fBcoatl --version\fR
Print version.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project wiki and language notes:
.br
\fBhttps://github.com/euxaristia/Coatl/wiki\fR
.br
\fBSPEC.md\fR in the Coatl repository.
